<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB7111F6313AFFE9364BFA60FDAE51F4" box="[264,627,1459,1482]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313AFFE9364BFA60FDB251F4" authority="Borgmeier, 1960: 337" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityPageNumber="337" authorityYear="1960" box="[264,623,1459,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pulicimyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B915EACA313AFFE9364BFA60FEA651F4" box="[264,379,1459,1482]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Pulicimyia</emphasis>
<treatmentCitation id="0AC010C9313AFFE936C1FA60FDB251F4" author="Borgmeier" box="[386,623,1459,1482]" page="337" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" year="1960">
<bibRefCitation id="EFF04B29313AFFE936C1FA60FDE451F4" author="Borgmeier" box="[386,569,1459,1482]" pageId="3" pageNumber="53" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1960) Gefluegelte und ungefluegelte Phoriden aus der Neotropischen Region, nebst Beschreibung von sieben neuen Gattungen (Diptera, Phoridae). Studia Entomologica, Petropolis, 3, 257 - 374." type="journal article" year="1960">
Borgmeier, 
<number id="3DA924FF313AFFE93543FA60FDE451F4" box="[512,569,1459,1482]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="1960.0">1960</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="3DA924FF313AFFE93507FA60FDB251F4" box="[580,623,1459,1482]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="337.0">337</number>
</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDE36D8313AFFEE364BFA28FD0755E8" blockId="3.[264,1325,1531,1877]" lastBlockId="4.[264,1323,284,470]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
Borgmeier distinguished this genus, which is only known from the females of three Neotropical species, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313AFFE93505F9F0FD0F5202" box="[582,722,1571,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Puliciphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B915EACA313AFFE93505F9F0FD0F5202" box="[582,722,1571,1596]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Puliciphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the possession of rudimentary halteres and an absence of an alar bristle (or any other wing rudiment). The examination of 
<typeStatus id="54DA887A313AFFE933CBF998FB25525B" box="[1160,1272,1611,1637]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">paratypes</typeStatus>
and other specimens of the 
<typeStatus id="54DA887A313AFFE93578F9A0FDB352B3" box="[571,622,1651,1677]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
species of this genus, 
<emphasis id="B915EACA313AFFE934E1F9A0FB8752B2" box="[930,1114,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313AFFE934E1F9A0FB8B52B2" box="[930,1110,1651,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pulicimyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">P. triangularis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
has allowed an examination, as slide mounts, of the supposed rudimentary halteres. As with the case of 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313AFFE93252F948FEAE52E2" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Ecitophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halterata">
<emphasis id="B915EACA313AFFE93252F948FEAE52E2" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">E. halterata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
discussed above, it is clear that the supposed halteres are in fact wing rudiments (
<figureCitation id="135A2A5D313AFFE93652F938FEBB533B" box="[273,358,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 24" captionStartId="13.[264,383,1275,1299]" captionTargetBox="[542,979,702,1231]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[506,1081,689,1249]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 24. Puliciphora triangularis: (22) female, abdominal tergite 5; (23) female, right wing rudiment; (24) male, left face of hypopygium. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169853/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA924FF313AFFE9360BF938FEBB533B" box="[328,358,1771,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
) that are intermediate in size between those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313AFFE934DAF938FB55533A" box="[921,1160,1771,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Puliciphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nuttingi">
<emphasis id="B915EACA313AFFE934DAF938FB55533A" box="[921,1160,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Puliciphora nuttingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="135A2A5D313AFFE933DAF938FB32533B" box="[1177,1263,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 11" captionStartId="4.[264,382,1465,1489]" captionTargetBox="[566,1013,527,1437]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[551,1036,494,1439]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 11. Puliciphora females: (8) P. occidentalis; right wing rudiment; (9) P. occidentalis; abdominal tergite 5; (10) P. nuttingi, right wing rudiment; (11) P. nuttingi, abdominal tergite 5. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169849/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA924FF313AFFE93392F938FB32533B" box="[1233,1263,1771,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) and the wing rudiment of 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313AFFE93577F8C0FBAA5313" authority="Melander &amp; Brues" authorityName="Melander &amp; Brues" box="[564,1143,1811,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Puliciphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B915EACA313AFFE93577F8C0FCBC5312" box="[564,865,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Puliciphora occidentalis</emphasis>
(Melander &amp; Brues)
</taxonomicName>
described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF04B29313AFFE9364BF8E8FE3C536B" author="Borgmeier" box="[264,481,1851,1877]" pageId="3" pageNumber="53" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1963) Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part I. The Phorinae, Aenigmatiinae and Metopininae, except Megaselia (Diptera, Phoridae). Studia Entomologica, Petropolis, 6, 1 - 256." type="journal article" year="1963">
Borgmeier (
<number id="3DA924FF313AFFE936D8F8E8FE05536B" box="[411,472,1851,1877]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="1963.0">1963</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as ‘a small papilla bearing a very short bristle’ (
<figureCitation id="135A2A5D313AFFE93316F8E8FB7F536B" box="[1109,1186,1851,1877]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 11" captionStartId="4.[264,382,1465,1489]" captionTargetBox="[566,1013,527,1437]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[551,1036,494,1439]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 11. Puliciphora females: (8) P. occidentalis; right wing rudiment; (9) P. occidentalis; abdominal tergite 5; (10) P. nuttingi, right wing rudiment; (11) P. nuttingi, abdominal tergite 5. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169849/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA924FF313AFFE933D1F8E8FB7F536B" box="[1170,1186,1851,1877]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Thus the supposed distinction between 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313DFFEE352FFECFFD36550B" box="[620,747,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pulicimyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B915EACA313DFFEE352FFECFFD36550B" box="[620,747,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Pulicimyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313DFFEE3465FECFFC6F550B" box="[806,946,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Puliciphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B915EACA313DFFEE3465FECFFC6F550B" box="[806,946,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Puliciphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females is negated. The former genus is therefore formally synonymised with the latter. Its three included species are therefore formally transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313DFFEE35E9FEBFFCEB55BB" box="[682,822,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Puliciphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B915EACA313DFFEE35E9FEBFFCEB55BB" box="[682,822,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Puliciphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below. This results in the Afrotropical species 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313DFFEE3627FE47FD8D5590" authority="Disney" authorityName="Disney" box="[356,592,404,430]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Puliciphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B915EACA313DFFEE3627FE47FE3E5593" box="[356,483,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">P. modesta</emphasis>
(Disney)
</taxonomicName>
becoming a homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C614D5B313DFFEE34C6FE47FB2F5590" authority="(Borgmeier) Comb." authorityName="(Borgmeier) Comb." box="[901,1266,404,430]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Puliciphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B915EACA313DFFEE34C6FE47FBD95593" box="[901,1028,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">P. modesta</emphasis>
(Borgmeier) 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22657B1313DFFEE33E0FE47FB2F5590" box="[1187,1266,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</taxonomicName>
nov. The former is therefore renamed below.
</paragraph>
